net.proteusframework.cms.component.generator

Interface Cacheable<P extends PageElement>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - page element type.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Generator<T>, ScriptGenerator<G>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractScriptGenerator, CmsIntegration, DelegateGenerator, GeneratorImpl, HTMLBoxGenerator, HTMLPageGenerator, MIWTGenerator, PageSyndicationGenerator, PassthroughGenerator, SequentialGenerator, XMLGenerator

    public interface Cacheable<P extends PageElement>
    Represents something that is responsible for generation or influences the generation of cacheable content.

    Users will call getIdentity(CmsRequest) prior to calling either getExpireTime() or getScope().

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

    • Method Detail

      • getExpireTime

        long getExpireTime()
        Get the expire time of the generated content.
        Returns:
        the expire time in millis or 0 if it expires immediately. Return -1 to indicate that the expire time from this Cacheable shouldn't be used unless otherwise specified.

      • getIdentity

        @Nullable
String getIdentity(CmsRequest<P> request)
        Return a string that uniquely identifies the information needed to generate or influence the content for the response.

        For example, if the response is dependent on a record from the database, an implementor should return a String representing the database key and a timestamp for when the record was last updated.

        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the identity of the generated content or null if unknown / unimplemented.

      • getScope

        net.proteusframework.internet.http.Scope getScope()
        Return the scope of the generated content that is the direct responsibility of your implementation.
        Returns:
        the scope.
